result.formatted_address: 7 Tin Lok Lane, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: Dim Dim Sum - Wan Chai

reviews.text:
3* feels generous, besides from the 'recommended dishes' which was a bit different from norm the rest felt like tourist food. 
The atmosphere was also very tourist with no locals eating there. 
If you want your local home country's 'Chinese food', this would best describe it. 

Prices were OK for dim sum.
It didn't look dirty as mentioned in other reviews.

Loved this restaurant. Came here three years ago and had yum cha for three days, absolutely yum! But this time it didn’t open till 10 am so we tried another shop nearby. 
Recommend this one compared to the same restaurant in Jordon.

What a fantastic place!! My favourite dim sum restaurant in the whole Hong Kong! I loved this place so much that I went there twice just to enjoy their fantastic dumplings. I tried many dishes from the menu but by far the best ones were truffle xiao long bao and dumplings with garlic chive, prawn and egg white - this one is a must, so delicious!! They take cash only but the prices are reasonable. Highly recommended place!
Nice tasty dim sum. Clean. Friendly staff. It deserves every bit of its good rating

Highly recommended seafood in pepper. ⭐️The dimsum flour for Hagao is very thin but chewy. I recommend to order rice noodle wrapped crispy fried shrimp. Their cream buns come in very cute little piggy shapes.
